The Meru county government has started an urban upgrading programme in Keeria market in Igoji East ward, South Imenti. It aims to enhance a 24-hour economy. Infrastructure executive Newton Itoobi said the county will establish a convenient drainage system. He said this will address business growth and enable quick and friendly exchange of goods and services in the market. Itoobi said improvements in sanitation and installation of cabros and floodlights will attract investors. Speaking in his office, the executive said funds have been set aside to upgrade other markets, towns and centres. &ldquo;This is an effort towards ensuring the promise made by Governor Peter Munya to upgrade our markets is fulfilled. We will ensure routine maintenance to generate more trade and attract investors,&rdquo; Itoobi said.